    <notes>
      <![CDATA[2.3 Equipment:
Items:
Language Stone:  This appears as a small jasper earring, which allows the wearer to read, write, and speak any language; archaic or coded languages may require a Static Mental Challenge to decipher.


Nightmare's Heart:  This object appears to be a small gold locket, its cover a cabochon jasper stone; inside is a tiny black mirror.  When the item is activated by opening the cover, the wielder may engage up to 5 targets in a Static Mental Challenge (no Traits risked); if the wielder is successful, his targets are struck with an onslaught of nightmarish images and may not take any action other than cowering or fleeing, though they may defend themselves if attacked.  This lasts until the wielder leaves the target's presence, or after 10 minutes have passed--whichever comes first.
Info:  Associate professor of Religious Studies, Arizona State University, Tempe Campus.  His office is located at ECA 344, and his office hours to his students are Tuesday and Thursday, 4:30-6 PM, Wednesday, 2-3 PM.  His areas of interest are the interactions between religion, mysticism, magic, and science, as well as the interpretation of symbolic, mythic and ritual principles as practiced in religion.]]>
    </notes>
  </mortal>
