  <item name="&quot;The Amazing Technicolor Dreamcoat&quot;" type="Artifact" subtype="Armor" level="0" bonus="0" amount="0" conceal="Jacket" lastmodified="5/28/2005 7:51:12 PM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2"/>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Fire-Retardant"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1">
      <trait name="Unique"/>
    </traitlist>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Reduce lethal damage to bashing. Two trait penalty to avoid the coat when thrusting/slashing. 

Firearms are not affected by coat's enchantment.]]>
    </powers>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[Requires the wearer give two extra blood traits upon putting the coat on.

Sunlight or supernatural fire will destroy the coat.]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
  <item name="(Artifacts and Devices)" type="Artifact" subtype="User Information" level="0" bonus="0" amount="0" lastmodified="12/2/2002 1:46:53 PM">
    <traitlist name="Tempers" abc="yes" display="2">
      <trait name="Click the &quot;Details&quot; Tab!"/>
    </traitlist>
    <traitlist name="Abilities" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Negatives" abc="yes" negative="yes" display="1"/>
    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Follow these instructions to load Artifacts and Devices into your game!]]>
    </powers>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[1. Click "Data Exchange" under the File menu.

2. Click the "Load Data" button.

3. Navigate to your Grapevine folder.  Select the file "Artifacts and Devices.gex" and click OK.

4. Click OK to confirm the list of loaded Artifacts and Devices and click Close to exit the Exchange Data window.

5. Done!  Enjoy the new items!]]>
    </appearance>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[White Wolf's copyright forbids me from redistributing the rules for each Artifact and Device.  "Artifacts and Devices.gex" provides book and page references instead. Fill out the item cards in detail as you need them, or colloborate with other STs to amass a complete collection.]]>
    </notes>
  </item>
