    <traitlist name="Availability" abc="yes" display="1"/>
    <powers>
      <![CDATA[Sarath’s Claw: Any weapon successfully engraved with the symbol of Sarrath (three curved claws tipped in blood) and empowered through the force of the drabarne's will becomes a weapon capable of doing great harm (aggravated damage) to all "magical" beings, including vampires, spirit-dwellers (spirit and Wraiths), faeries and all types of werecreatures . In addition to the immediate damage, the weapon has a chance of inflicting additional wound levels in the five succeeding rounds as small pieces of the claw work their way deeper into the target's body. In each of the five rounds after the claw first hits a creature, the target must make a successful Physical Challenge (plus an additional trait for each level of Fortitude for vampires) (difficulty of the wielder's Willpower) or take an additional level of lethal damage.  The magic of Sarrath's Claw on a victim is not cumulative. Further attacks from the claw will do immediate damage to an already affected victim, but not any more additional damage. However, once the effects of the first attack are over (five rounds), a new success with the claw will start the process anew.]]>
    </powers>
  </item>
