  <location name="McGinty's" type="Bar" level="0" owner="Justin Case" access="Private" securitytraits="7" securityretests="4" gauntlet="7" affinity="Fae" lastmodified="1/25/2004 9:19:56 AM">
    <traitlist name="Links" abc="yes" atomic="yes" display="5"/>
    <where>
      <![CDATA[Club is 1/2 mile from US 60, off of Silly Mountain Rd.  (out by Ren Fairegrounds)]]>
    </where>
    <appearance>
      <![CDATA[Club designed to look like two story wooden English pub house.

Secondary Haven for Justin]]>
    </appearance>
    <security>
      <![CDATA[Outside Security: 

Club is 1/2 mile from US 60, off of Silly Mountain Rd.  (out by Ren Fairegrounds)  The Club driveway is 500 yards, and passes past a 12 foot high security fence that surrounds the property at a distance of 200 yards away from club.  Occasionally Security patrols will walk this perimeter.  (3 security guards on patrol all armed with submachine guns.)

Parking lot is paved and surrounds the building on three sides.  The rear of the club is packed dirt and is where employees park.   Large halogen security lights are mounted at each roof corner providing illumination of the parking lot area, along with several lamp posts placed throughout the parking area.   

Main Entrance:  
Tunnel entrance. (The Alley)  30 Foot Long.  Steel Floor.  Mirrored Walls.  

Entryway has recessed fans set up in far wall blowing slight breeze towards the outside entrance.  This breeze is strong enough to push smoke out of the club and is used to detect Mist Formed individuals entering the club.  

Entrance Doors: 
Steel Doors  (Recessed in Ceiling, Cover Floor to Ceiling (14 Traits and 10 Health Levels)) Upon Security Shutdown, doors are released and drop into recessed grooves in floor at Fleetness.  Any attempt to stop doors from dropping is winning two consecutive Static Physical Tests against 14 Traits, must have Puissance to continue holding door and must retest every turn.

At outer Entrance is Guard/Bouncer at a podium who checks all incoming guests.   A buzzer is pressed to allow guests entrance into the club.  The buzzer must be pressed as guests enter.  If not, the pressure sensors in the floor of the hallway will activate and open the pit.  

Hallway is actually trapdoor over pit.  Trapdoor is secured via 5 braces along north side.  Upon Lockdown, the braces retract and door swings down at Fleetness.  Beneath the trap door is a Steel Lined pit.  Pit is 30 feet long, 30 feet deep and 10 feet wide.  Pit can be set up in following configurations: 

1.	Stakes:  Stakes are screwed into the floor every 3 feet.  Any persons falling in pit must make Static Physical against 8 traits to avoid falling on a stake.  (Athletics and dodge for retests for falling persons.)
2.	Gas Pit: Filled 10 Feet deep with jet Fuel.  Small tube runs from security room to Pit wall 25 feet up the wall.  When needed, incendiary device can be dropped into pit, igniting fuel.  All characters in the pit suffer 1 level of Aggravated damage per turn.]]>
    </security>
    <umbra>
      <![CDATA[Club is a "trod" for Changelings due to continuous use of Chimestry generating Glamour.]]>
    </umbra>
    <notes>
      <![CDATA[(Owner: Tony Padua) 
Silly Mountain Road, Apache Junction, AZ

All Walls unless otherwise noted are considered to be Concrete reinforced with steel plating covered by wood paneling.  All Interior walls are considered to have 14 traits and 5 Health levels per 10 foot area.  

All rooms are normal sized rooms (12 foot ceiling) unless otherwise noted.  

Camera Units: Dual camera setups near ceiling.  Both cameras sweep in opposing 180 degree arcs left/right with lens capable of viewing entire range from floor to ceiling. Also contains microphone unit.  Can be controlled remotely from Security Room to stop movement and focus in on specific location.  

Chain Guns: 
Bonus Traits: 5
Negative Traits: Loud, Clumsy
Damage:  3 Health Levels.
Special Ability: Spray: A chain gun may effect up to five targets if they are standing immediately next to one another and are further than 10 feet from the gun.  Fully Automatic: Can cause an extra health level of damage to a single target standing within five feet.

The gun is manned by security personnel in the Security Booth.  Stats for standard security person: 8 Mental traits, Firearms x3 (Specialization: Chain Gun). The guns are belt fed with standard ammuntiion (2000 rounds).   The guns are mounted on motorized mounts, capable of 180 degree field of fire left and right, with 90 degree up and down.  

Main Room:  
Ceiling: 20 Feet high. 
	
Walls are wood covered.  Several plants located throughout room.  

Normal furniture, arranged like a large pub house gathering room.  Large video monitors (61" TV screen) against far wall (alleyway brick wall).  Normally showing sports programming , but can accept feed from Security Room.  

Cyber Café:  
Ceiling: 12 foot high (normal).   Bar area and cyber lounge.  Several computer systems allowing access to general internet are available for use by club patrons.  Bar is well stocked, but normally does not have Blood Bar (only if noted prior to game). 3 Payphones also available in this area.

Lounge Area: 

Ceiling: 12 foot high (normal).   Overstuffed Sofas littered throughout area.  Small stage area for live musicians.   Large marble fireplace located against wall (outer wall of room).  Provided for customers wishing to relax and talk with friends without having to shout over music.  This room has a lockable door for private meetings.  Standard door (9 Traits, 4 Health Levels) with normal lock (Mental Challenge versus 10 traits to pick/unlock)

Battle Pit (normally the hot tub area): 

Only accessable through elevator.  Located 40 feet below club.   

Ceiling: 35 Foot high.   All Walls, Floor and Ceiling are steel plating covering cement.  
Room has stadium style seating in 270 degree arc around the battle pit itself, with seating for 60 people.  
The pit itself is circular and 20 feet in diameter and recessed 10 feet into the ground.   Ladders are provided for access to the floor of the pit. 

Security Office: 
 (Located on Second Floor, accessed through elevator).  Contains bank of separate video monitors for each camera and computer system to control views on main display.  Also has controls for Chain gun systems.   

Each camera is set up on a VCR system to record all events occurring through 24 hours.  Each tape is reviewed the next evening by Justin and is either stored as evidence or erased and reset for the next evening.  

The door security is keyed to fingerprint ID for Justin and Jared or keypad entry (all security has code, Mental Challenge versus 14 traits to attempt to crack).  Access can be granted from within the office through controls on the main desk.  

Office Door:  (10 Traits, 6 Health Levels).  In case of emergency, secondary door slides down from ceiling and secures the room.  Second Door has 14 Traits and 10 Health Levels.

Secret Exit: Exit located within the Security room.  Elevator down to level of the Battle Pit with access to either Battle Pit area (through hidden door) or to tunnel that runs away from the club for 300 yards and exits through trap door that is secured and can only be opened from within the tunnel.  Entrances are secured with fingerprint id scanners set to Justin and Jared only.]]>
    </notes>
  </location>
